HEADWORD: Beblubber
<hw>Be*blub"ber</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To make
swollen and disfigured or sullied by weeping; <as>as, her eyes or cheeks
were <ex>beblubbered</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

